5. The amplifying circuit of claim 4, wherein the supply voltage adjusting circuit comprises:
an input for receiving an original supply voltage;
an output for outputting the variable supply voltage;
a plurality of capacitors coupled to the input and the output; and
a plurality of switches respectively coupled to at least one of the input, the output, and the capacitors, each of the switches being switched on or off according to the control signal.

